# =============================================================================
# .env.example
# =============================================================================
# Copy to `.env.local` for local development. NEVER commit `.env.local` —
# it is in `.gitignore`. In production, set these in Vercel project settings
# (`vercel env add`).
# =============================================================================

# Shared secret used to authenticate Vercel Cron invocations of the
# /api/cron/predictions route. The cron platform sends this as
# `Authorization: Bearer ${CRON_SECRET}`.
#
# Behaviour by environment:
#   - production : REQUIRED. Missing or mismatched secret returns 401.
#   - development: OPTIONAL. If omitted, the route allows unauthenticated
#                  requests for ergonomic local testing only.
CRON_SECRET=replace-me-in-vercel-project-settings

# =============================================================================
# Supabase — server-only credentials (Phase 7+)
# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are read ONLY on the server. They
# are consumed by `src/lib/data/supabase/serverClient.ts` and the
# Supabase-backed repositories in `src/lib/data/persistence/supabase/`.
#
# CRITICAL SECURITY RULES:
#   - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY bypasses Row-Level Security and grants full
#     database access. It is NEVER exposed to the browser.
#   - Do NOT prefix either variable with NEXT_PUBLIC_. The NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix
#     would embed the value in the client bundle. A `server-only` import on the
#     client module raises a build error as a backstop.
#   - Do NOT import the server client from React components or any code that
#     ends up in the client bundle. A vocabulary scan over `src/components/**`
#     fails the build if a Supabase import sneaks in.
#   - Do NOT commit real values. `.env*.local` and `.env*` are gitignored.
#
# Phase 7A status: the Supabase repositories exist and are tested with mocked
# clients, but the deployed public UI still reads from a server-only demo data
# helper (`src/lib/data/demoPredictions.ts`). Leaving these variables unset
# is safe — the app continues to operate in demo/mock mode.
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# Neon / Vercel Postgres — server-only credentials (Phase 7C+, preferred)
# =============================================================================
# These variables are auto-created by the Vercel Marketplace Neon integration
# (Project Settings → Storage → Connect Neon). They are populated into the
# Production and Preview environments by Vercel; `vercel env pull .env.local`
# fetches them for local development.
#
# - POSTGRES_URL              — pooled connection string used by the runtime
#                                (cron route, repositories).
# - POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING  — direct connection string for migration scripts
#                                and other long-lived operations.
#
# CRITICAL SECURITY RULES:
#   - Both URLs contain database credentials. They are NEVER exposed to the
#     browser. The Postgres server client (`src/lib/data/postgres/serverClient.ts`)
#     uses `import 'server-only'` as a build-time backstop.
#   - Do NOT prefix either variable with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
#   - Do NOT commit real values. `.env*.local` and `.env*` are gitignored.
#
# Priority ordering when multiple persistence backends are configured (see
# `src/lib/data/persistence/repositoryFactory.ts`):
#   1. POSTGRES_URL                                   → Neon Postgres adapter
#   2. SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY       → Supabase adapter
#   3. neither                                        → in-memory (demo mode)
#
# Phase 7C status: the Postgres repositories exist and are tested with mocked
# clients. The cron route still uses in-memory repositories — wiring to
# `createPredictionRepository()` is deferred to Phase 7D. Leaving these unset
# is safe — the app continues to operate in demo/mock mode.
POSTGRES_URL=
POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING=
